\f2\u-10179?\u-8903?\f1  \f0 LEADERBOARD & RANKING (126\f1\endash 170)\par
How is my leaderboard rank calculated?\par
\par
Your rank is calculated based on your total performance score. This score is a weighted sum of verified projects, approved certificates, achievements, profile completion, activity streak, and other contribution metrics. The system automatically recalculates rank whenever your score changes.\par
\par
What factors influence my rank the most?\par
\par
Verified projects and major achievements usually carry higher weight. Certificates, GitHub linking, and consistent activity also contribute significantly. The exact weight distribution is defined by system rules.\par
\par
Does verification impact my rank?\par
\par
Yes. Only verified or approved submissions contribute full points. Pending or rejected entries do not affect your ranking.\par
\par
Is the leaderboard updated in real time?\par
\par
The leaderboard updates automatically whenever there is a change in score, such as approval of a project or certificate.\par
\par
Can two students have the same rank?\par
\par
If two students have equal scores, they may temporarily share rank position until further differentiation occurs.\par
\par
Is there a department-wise leaderboard?\par
\par
Yes. Students are ranked both overall and within their department to encourage healthy competition.\par
\par
Is there a year-wise leaderboard?\par
\par
Yes. Rankings can be filtered based on academic year to ensure fair comparison among peers.\par
\par
What is the difference between overall rank and department rank?\par
\par
Overall rank compares all students across departments, while department rank compares students within the same department only.\par
\par
Does profile completion affect leaderboard?\par
\par
Yes. A fully completed profile contributes additional points and improves visibility.\par
\par
Does activity streak impact rank?\par
\par
Yes. Consistent engagement and regular updates may provide bonus points.\par
\par
Can the admin reset the leaderboard?\par
\par
Yes. Admins may reset rankings in special circumstances such as a new academic cycle.\par
\par
What happens if my score decreases?\par
\par
If a submission is removed or revoked, your score may decrease and rank may change accordingly.\par
\par
Can I see my previous rank history?\par
\par
If analytics are enabled, historical ranking data may be visible in your dashboard.\par
\par
Do rejected submissions affect rank?\par
\par
Rejected submissions do not contribute points and therefore do not improve rank.\par
\par
Are leaderboard scores transparent?\par
\par
Yes. The scoring system follows predefined logic to ensure fairness.\par
\par
Does quantity matter more than quality?\par
\par
No. Verified and quality submissions generally carry more weight than unverified bulk entries.\par
\par
Can I improve rank without adding projects?\par
\par
Yes. You can improve rank by adding certificates, achievements, completing your profile, and maintaining activity.\par
\par
Is leaderboard visible publicly outside the platform?\par
\par
No. It is visible only to registered users within the platform.\par
\par
Can ranking influence placements?\par
\par
SPMS ranking can serve as a performance indicator but official placement decisions depend on institutional policies.\par
\par
Does deleting a project affect my rank?\par
\par
Yes. Removing a verified project will reduce your score.\par
\par
Is leaderboard sorted automatically?\par
\par
Yes. It is automatically sorted in descending order based on total score.\par
\par
Do admins appear in leaderboard?\par
\par
No. Only student accounts are ranked.\par
\par
Can leaderboard rules change?\par
\par
Yes. Admin may adjust scoring weights for fairness.\par
\par
Are monthly leaderboards available?\par
\par
If enabled, monthly rankings may be displayed.\par
\par
Is ranking competitive?\par
\par
Yes. The leaderboard is designed to encourage healthy academic competition.\par
